        "timestamp": 1781788855
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>After refresh:<br>\n<img alt=\"image.png\" class=\"inline-image\" data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"553x169\" data-original-src=\"/user_uploads/53090/VqSbtuScYOe5BhX8Jd8xxzRU/image.png\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/53090/VqSbtuScYOe5BhX8Jd8xxzRU/image.png/840x560.webp\"></p>",
        "id": 604530263,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Vila",
        "timestamp": 1781789490
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, so you're seeing this without the ELB. Hmm.</p>\n<p>It must have something to do with the jsessionid, right? It appears in the URL for the first load in an incognito window, for example.</p>",
        "id": 604531509,
        "sender_full_name": "Philip Durbin 🚀",
        "timestamp": 1781789687
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right</p>",
        "id": 604532043,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Vila",
        "timestamp": 1781789778
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It seems to happen only in the latest versions.</p>",
        "id": 604532872,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Vila",
        "timestamp": 1781789911
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It works fine from a fresh docker compose env: <a href=\"https://guides.dataverse.org/en/6.10.1/container/running/demo.html#quickstart\">https://guides.dataverse.org/en/6.10.1/container/running/demo.html#quickstart</a></p>\n<p>This environment only has Payara, though, so when I go to <a href=\"http://localhost:8080\">http://localhost:8080</a> I'm not hitting any sort of proxy like Apache.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-18 at 9.44.27 AM.png\" class=\"inline-image\" data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1250x828\" data-original-src=\"/user_uploads/53090/1CN90n0F6D6MnRDgo-lHbrAc/Screenshot-2026-06-18-at-9.44.27AM.png\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/53090/1CN90n0F6D6MnRDgo-lHbrAc/Screenshot-2026-06-18-at-9.44.27AM.png/840x560.webp\"></p>",
